Thank you for using RAPIS FIMC! RAPIS FIMC is an anagram for PRACISIMF, which means "Please remove all columns I specified in my file" ¯\_(ツ)_/¯. Thats the only purpose of this program.
Select a file by clicking on "Browse". Then click "Load" to load the file into the program.
After that, you can either select columns in the text file by highlighting them with your mouse, or use the spinner boxes in the lower left corner. Be careful, for you can only select columns located on the same row. If your selection spans over more than one line, the program will reset it back to the previously marked content.
When you selected the columns you want to be removed from the file, click on "Start". You can now specify the name and location of the file.
Thats it. When you open the file you just saved, you should now see the exact file you loaded, but with the specified columns removed.
As for now, the following files are supported: *.txt, *.tsv, *.csv, *.htm, *.html, *.log
This program is created by Sunburst275. If you want to request a feature, give feedback, ask a question or just want to get in contact with me, click on the "Sunburst275"-Button. You will be redirected to my website. There you can go to "Contact" to contact me directly, or see a walkthrough and more information about this program.
Thank you very much!
